Challenger Financial Services Group
Ltd.  climbed to the highest since January 2008 in Sydney trading
after the investment manager said it plans to buy back as much
as 10 percent of its stock.  The stock rose as much as 7.7 percent to A$4.77 and ended
at A$4.60 at the 4:10 p.m. local time close. Australiaâ€™s
benchmark  S&P/ASX 200  Index was little changed at 4,619.90.  Sydney-based Challenger said it will seek shareholder
approval at its annual general meeting on Nov. 18 to buy as many
as 50.27 million shares over the coming year. The company
acquired 73.5 million of its shares in the 12 months through Oct.
1, Challenger said today in a notice to shareholders posted to
